<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Gemini Data Analytics on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cloudgda/</link><description>Recent content in Gemini Data Analytics on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cloudgda/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Gemini Data Analytics Source</title><link>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cloudgda/source/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mcp-toolbox.dev/dev/integrations/cloudgda/source/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about"&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;cloud-gemini-data-analytics&lt;/code&gt; source provides a client to interact with the &lt;a href="https://docs.cloud.google.com/gemini/docs/conversational-analytics-api/reference/rest"&gt;Gemini Data Analytics API&lt;/a&gt;. This allows tools to send natural language queries to the API.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Authentication can be handled in two ways:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application Default Credentials (ADC) (Recommended):&lt;/strong&gt; By default, the source uses ADC to authenticate with the API. The Toolbox server will fetch the credentials from its running environment (server-side authentication). This is the recommended method.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client-side OAuth:&lt;/strong&gt; If &lt;code&gt;useClientOAuth&lt;/code&gt; is set to &lt;code&gt;true&lt;/code&gt;, the source expects the authentication token to be provided by the caller when making a request to the Toolbox server (typically via an HTTP Bearer token). The Toolbox server will then forward this token to the underlying Gemini Data Analytics API calls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id="available-tools"&gt;Available Tools&lt;/h2&gt;








 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 







